snippet.textDisplay: I don't think these type of sword games are that good. I dislike the giant boss thing. The best games don't require gamers to have fast reflexes or remember complex button combos. If they could make a game where enemies are easily beatable with a simple strategy that often works better because the story moves forward without replays of the same fights. I look at games like this and I see so much wrong. I like the idea of needing to use different strategies to beat different enemies but I hate boss fights that drag on for a long time. The concept of finding a weak spot or needing a special weapon or skill ability is more fun. People just want to win
